      <title>Layer.provideLayer</title>
      <link>http://localhost:3000/reference/capability/m-layer-providelayer/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:3000/reference/capability/m-layer-providelayer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;fsdocs-usage&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span&gt;Layer.provideLayer&amp;#32;&lt;span&gt;layer&amp;#32;flow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Provides a derived environment from a layer flow to a downstream flow.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;parameters&#34;&gt;Parameters&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;layer&lt;/code&gt;: &lt;code&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://adz.github.io/FsFlow/reference/FsFlow/fsflow-flow-3.html&#34;&gt;Flow&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;lsquo;input, &amp;rsquo;error, &amp;rsquo;environment&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;flow&lt;/code&gt;: &lt;code&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://adz.github.io/FsFlow/reference/FsFlow/fsflow-flow-3.html&#34;&gt;Flow&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;lsquo;environment, &amp;rsquo;error, &amp;lsquo;value&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Requires</title>
      <link>http://localhost:3000/reference/capability/t-requires-1/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:3000/reference/capability/t-requires-1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Describes the capability contract for a single dependency.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;remarks&#34;&gt;Remarks&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Named capability interfaces inherit this contract once and then expose the dependency through a&#xA;member such as &lt;code&gt;Clock&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;Logger&lt;/code&gt;. Workflow builders can accept any environment&#xA;that implements &lt;code&gt;Requires&amp;lt;&#39;dep&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;, which lets larger runtimes satisfy smaller&#xA;boundaries.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Resolver.resolve</title>
      <link>http://localhost:3000/reference/capability/m-resolver-resolve/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:3000/reference/capability/m-resolver-resolve/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;fsdocs-usage&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span&gt;Resolver.resolve&amp;#32;&lt;span&gt;projection&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Reads a dependency from the environment using the provided projection.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;parameters&#34;&gt;Parameters&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;projection&lt;/code&gt;: &lt;code&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;lsquo;env -&amp;gt; &amp;lsquo;resolve&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Resolve</title>
      <link>http://localhost:3000/reference/capability/t-resolve-2/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:3000/reference/capability/t-resolve-2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Request token for projecting a value from a dependency.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;remarks&#34;&gt;Remarks&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Builders read the dependency from the environment, apply the projection, and then reuse the&#xA;existing lift/bind behavior for the projected value. If the projection returns a&#xA;&lt;code&gt;Result&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;Async&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;Task&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;ValueTask&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;ColdTask&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;option&lt;/code&gt;, or&#xA;&lt;code&gt;voption&lt;/code&gt;, the existing workflow rules still apply.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Resolve</title>
      <link>http://localhost:3000/reference/capability/t-resolve-1/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:3000/reference/capability/t-resolve-1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Request token for binding a whole dependency inside a workflow.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;remarks&#34;&gt;Remarks&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use this token when a workflow needs the dependency itself rather than a value projected from&#xA;that dependency. The &lt;code&gt;flow {}&lt;/code&gt; builder and its internal compatibility helpers&#xA;read it from any environment that implements &lt;code&gt;Requires&amp;lt;&#39;dep&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
